# Project North Star, Cursor Rules

Read these rules before writing any code. Every rule is a hard requirement.

---

## Tokens, always, no exceptions

- Never use hardcoded color values. No hex codes, no rgb(), no Tailwind color utilities like bg-blue-500 or text-red-400.
- Always use semantic tokens: bg-background, text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, border-border, bg-card, text-primary, bg-primary, text-destructive, etc.
- Never use primitive tokens (--primitive-neutral-15) directly in components. They exist only inside theme CSS files.
- If a semantic token doesn't exist for what you need, stop and ask before inventing one.

---

## Typography, exact fonts, exact usage

- Bitter (font-heading), all headings h1 through h6, weight 400 only.
- Atkinson Hyperlegible (font-sans), all body text and UI labels.
- Atkinson Hyperlegible Mono (font-mono), code blocks and monospace only.
- Never use any other font family.
- Never apply font-bold, font-semibold, or font-medium to heading elements.

---

## Heading sizes, use the defined scale

- h1 → text-4xl + font-heading (Bitter)
- h2 → text-3xl + font-heading (Bitter)
- h3 → text-2xl + font-heading (Bitter)
- h4 → text-xl + font-heading (Bitter)
- h5 → text-lg + font-heading (Bitter)
- h6 → text-base + font-heading (Bitter)
- Never rely on browser heading defaults, Tailwind preflight resets them.

---

## Border radius, near zero by design

- Use rounded-sm, rounded-md, or rounded-lg from the design system radius scale.
- Never use rounded-full on non-circular elements.
- Never add arbitrary radius values.

---

## Components, use what exists

- Before writing any UI element, check src/components/ui/ and public/registry.json.
- If a component exists in the registry, use it. Never re-implement it inline.
- Components are built on Base UI primitives for accessibility. Do not replace them with plain HTML elements.

---

## TypeScript, strict always

- All props must be strictly typed with union types. No loose string where 'primary' | 'secondary' is correct.
- Export types for every component.
- Add JSDoc comments to every prop, required, not optional.
- Zero TypeScript errors before any task is complete.

---

## SSR safety

- Never reference window, document, or navigator outside of a useEffect or a "use client" component.
- All components must render correctly on the server.

---

## What never to do

- No style={{ color: '#hex' }} or any inline style with a raw value
- No bg-blue-500 or any Tailwind color outside semantic tokens
- No font-bold on Bitter
- No rounded-full on non-circular elements
- No hardcoded pixel values for spacing, use Tailwind spacing utilities
- No skipping JSDoc on new components
- No committing with TypeScript errors
- No duplicating a component that already exists in src/components/ui/
- No browser globals outside useEffect

---

## Theming

- Two themes: ag (default) and navy.
- Dark mode uses the .dark class on <html>. Semantic tokens handle both modes automatically.
- Never hardcode light-only or dark-only values.

---

## Token architecture (three tiers, never skip one)

Primitive → Semantic → Component

- Primitives: raw oklch values in globals.css. Never used in components.
- Semantic: meaning-based tokens in src/themes/. Used in all components.
- Component: scoped tokens like --sidebar-* and --chart-*.

---

## Adding a new component

1. Create src/components/ui/[name].tsx with strict TypeScript types and JSDoc on every prop
2. Add entry to src/lib/registry.ts
3. Add renderer case in src/components/registry/component-renderer.tsx
4. Add code generator case in src/lib/code-generator.ts
5. Run: npm run registry:generate
6. Run: npx tsc --noEmit, zero errors required
7. Update CHANGELOG.md

---

## Governance

- All changes require team approval before merging.
- AI-generated code is for scaffolding only, always review before merging.
- Every release updates CHANGELOG.md.
